    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Nageia excelsa are anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant activities. Anti-inflammatory properties of Nageia excelsa are due to the presence of flavonoids, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. The antimicrobial properties of this plant are attributed to saponins, which have been found to exhibit broad-spectrum activity against various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. Additionally, the antioxidant properties of Nageia excelsa are a result of the presence of volatile oils, which have been shown to scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The anti-diabetic and anti-hypertensive properties of this plant are also attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which have been found to improve insulin sensitivity and reduce blood pressure.",
