    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Nageia excelsa are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and terpenoids, which have been isolated and characterized. Flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol have been shown to exhibit antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities, contributing to the plant's potential healing properties. Phenolic acids like ferulic acid and sinapic acid have been found to possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, while terpenoids like nageic acid and nageic alcohol have been reported to have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory activities. Additionally, the plant's essential oil contains compounds such as \u03b1-pinene, \u03b2-pinene, and limonene, which have been shown to have antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory effects. These constituents collectively contribute to Nageia excelsa's potential therapeutic benefits.",
