    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Nageia excelsa are derived from its leaves and bark. Infusion is made by steeping dried leaves in hot water to create a medicinal tea used to treat fever and rheumatism. A tincture is obtained through the percolation of leaves in a solvent, which is used to treat coughs and respiratory issues. Decoction is prepared by boiling the bark in water to create a remedy for various ailments including digestive issues. A salve is prepared by infusing the leaves in oil to create a topical application for wounds and skin irritations.",
